      • addPark

        public boolean addPark(java.lang.String name,
                       java.lang.String description,
                       double snowChange)
        Returns true if the Park is added to the list and false otherwise. The method constructs a Park using the provided parameters and creates a unique parkID for the Park using the numParks as described above. The Park is added to the parks list so that the list is always sorted by Park name. Observers of ParkList are notified of the change if the Park is added to the parks list. You will not be able to use Collections.sort() for this method.
        Parameters:
        name - of the park to add
        description - of the park to add
        snowChange - of the park to add
        Returns:
        true if added correctly

      • getParkAt

        public Park getParkAt(int idx)
        Returns the Park at the given index in the list. If the index is less than 0 or the index is greater or equal to size() an IndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown.
        Parameters:

        Park at given index

      • update

        public void update(java.util.Observable ob,
                   java.lang.Object obj)
        If a Park in the ParkList changes, the update() method is automatically called. ParkList should propagate the notification of the change to its Observers IF the Observable o is contained in the parks list of Parks. The arg parameter is passed to notifyObservers().
        Specified by:
        update in interface java.util.Observer
        Parameters:
        ob - Observable pattern
        obj - element to update

      • indexOfID

        public int indexOfID(java.lang.String parkID)
        Returns the index of the first occurrence of a Park that has an exact match to the provided parkID or -1 if there are no Parks with an exact match on the given parkID.
        Parameters:
        parkID - to look up in the list
        Returns:
        returnVal index of the park with given id or -1 if parkID doesn't exist

      • get2DArray

        public java.lang.Object[][] get2DArray()
        Returns an Object[][] array. Each row, i, contains a Park. [i][0] is the Park parkID, [i][1] is the Park name, [i][2] is the Park description, and [i][3] is the Park snowChange.
        Specified by:
        get2DArray in interface Tabular
        Returns:
        Object[][] with Park
